You can use the following code to redirect to a URL from PHP using HTML meta:

```
<?php
$url = "http://www.example.com";
echo "<html>";
echo "<head>";
echo "<meta http-equiv='refresh' content='0;URL=".$url."'>";
echo "</head>";
echo "</html>";
?>
```

In this code, replace "http://www.example.com" with the URL you want to redirect to. The "content" attribute in the meta tag specifies the amount of time before the redirect occurs (in this case, 0 seconds).

